defaultThe aim of the CJD resource centre and its oversight committee is to ensure fair and appropriate access to extremely rare blood components from clinical cases of 
defaultvCJD
default.  Samples used in these studies were generated by NIBSC in collaboration with other TSE research groups who supplied animal samples (AHVLA and 
defaultRoslin
default); the CJD Surveillance unit and the MRC 
defaultPrion
default clinic who provided CJD samples and the UK National Blood and Transfusion Service who provided normal donor samples.  Both test sensitivity (how little infectious material can be detected) and specificity (number of samples incorrectly scored positive) studies were performed.  
